==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Racemic
<hw>Ra*ce"mic</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧*s⟦emac⟧"m⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>rac⟦eacute⟧mique</ets>. See <er>Raceme</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid found in
many kinds of grapes. It is also obtained from tartaric acid, with which
it is isomeric, and from sugar, gum, etc., by oxidation. It is a sour
white crystalline substance, consisting of a combination of
dextrorotatory and levorotatory tartaric acids.</def>
<rj><au>Gregory.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Racemiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
